164
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,920
Should I sing a requiem?

165
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:01,300
Sounds can kill people, so be careful.

166
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:16,530
I'll die even if you pet me.

167
00:11:16,530 --> 00:11:18,980
That's news to me.

168
00:11:20,820 --> 00:11:23,780
<i>He always acts contrary to how he feels.</i>

169
00:11:23,780 --> 00:11:26,560
<i>I think I get him a bit better now.</i>

170
00:11:29,260 --> 00:11:33,920
<i>An ambiguous feeling
that's a bit different from reality.</i>

171
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:36,300
Mikoto.

172
00:11:36,980 --> 00:11:40,540
I got Jin's diary.
You said you wanted first dibs.

173
00:12:12,310 --> 00:12:14,100
<i>A dream?</i>

174
00:12:19,060 --> 00:12:23,220
<i>Is this Mr. Haiba from high school?</i>

175
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:27,300
<i>It's probably my imagination,
since I've never seen it.</i>

176
00:12:27,820 --> 00:12:29,960
<i>And yet...</i>

177
00:12:30,490 --> 00:12:34,820
<i>Mr. Haiba's old self doesn't seem too friendly.</i>

178
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:42,140
