196
00:14:07,610 --> 00:14:10,870
You made that happen. It's your dream.

197
00:14:10,870 --> 00:14:14,300
You spelled "failure" wrong. It should be...

198
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:17,920
High School Girl.

199
00:14:22,690 --> 00:14:26,780
This is a dream. Who cares about that?

200
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:29,110
Don't just grow up randomly. That scared me.

201
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:31,250
You made this happen too.

202
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:33,910
It's a reflection of your fantasies.

203
00:14:33,910 --> 00:14:35,170
Fan...

204
00:14:35,170 --> 00:14:36,840
So...

205
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:43,640
You can do whatever you want in your dream.

206
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:45,900
There are no laws here.

207
00:14:47,230 --> 00:14:49,020
That's...

208
00:15:26,310 --> 00:15:27,840
Give me some shaved ice.

209
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,910
Jin, you're finally headed home?

210
00:15:29,910 --> 00:15:31,930
Yeah. It's so hot outside.

211
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:34,050
Mikoto's here.

212
00:15:34,050 --> 00:15:35,470
Really? Why?

213
00:15:35,470 --> 00:15:37,900
She was waiting for you.

214
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:39,900
Forget the shaved ice.

215
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,970
High School Girl.

216
00:15:44,970 --> 00:15:47,380
You're late, Mr. Haiba.

217
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:51,830
I almost fell asleep waiting for you.

218
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:55,360
I see. Nice bedhead.

219
00:15:57,450 --> 00:15:59,840
Why were you waiting?

220
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:02,940
I wanted you to help me with
my physics homework again this year.

221
00:16:02,940 --> 00:16:05,470
Why not at my house?

222
00:16:05,470 --> 00:16:10,520
When we're alone, you joke around more.

223
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:24,790
And I might fall asleep at your house.

224
00:16:27,530 --> 00:16:29,660
Bedhead's on the other side.

225
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:37,960
Why are you trying to hide it?

226
00:16:40,230 --> 00:16:41,540
There, there.

227
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:45,400
You're diligent with your homework
again this year. What a good student.

228
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,220
That's sarcasm.

229
00:16:47,220 --> 00:16:50,240
So, how many pages left?

230
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:51,780
One page.

231
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:55,290
Stop being a good student.
Did you really want to study with me?

232
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:59,145
You're giving me too much praise.

233
00:16:59,145 --> 00:17:01,535
It was only twice.

234
00:17:01,535 --> 00:17:05,650
<i>Dang it. He said it once in my dream.</i>

235
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:09,630
I only became studious recently.

236
00:17:09,630 --> 00:17:13,650
Before high school, I'd do my homework
last-minute like a delinquent.

237
00:17:13,650 --> 00:17:15,960
That makes you a delinquent?

238
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:18,860
But I can't imagine that from you.

239
00:17:18,860 --> 00:17:23,700
It's because I had a diary.

240
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:26,300
A one-sentence diary.

241
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:29,540
I think I understand.

242
00:17:30,130 --> 00:17:32,380
The empty space never fills up.

243
00:17:32,380 --> 00:17:34,720
You should've just written whatever.

244
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,580
Are you telling me to lie?

245
00:17:36,580 --> 00:17:39,180
No, I'm not.

246
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:42,450
Things like, "I wish
I could've hung out with friends."

247
00:17:42,450 --> 00:17:45,940
"I wish we had a family vacation."

248
00:17:45,940 --> 00:17:48,300
Just write about your wishes.

249
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:50,710
Because those aren't lies.

250
00:17:50,710 --> 00:17:53,800
They feel just as empty as lies though.

251
00:17:58,810 --> 00:18:00,360
Then...

252
00:18:01,476 --> 00:18:03,840
in your diary...

253
00:18:04,730 --> 00:18:07,460
did you write your wishes?

254
00:18:08,070 --> 00:18:09,870
Hm...

255
00:18:09,870 --> 00:18:13,920
Who knows? I forgot.

256
00:18:15,770 --> 00:18:19,560
Well, that's not important.

257
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:30,060
Hurry up and finish so I can flirt with you.

258
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:39,118
<i>Whether it's my dream or in reality,</i>

